any endothelial cell of artery that is part of a coronary artery.

pyramidal neurons have a pyramid-shaped soma with a single axon, a large apical dendrite and multiple basal dendrites. the apex and an apical dendrite typically point toward the pial surface and other dendrites and an axon emerging from the base. the axons may have local collaterals but also project outside their region. pyramidal neurons are found in the cerebral cortex, the hippocampus, and the amygdala.
a dendritic cell of the myeloid lineage.
a mature sexual reproductive cell of the female germline.
gr1-low non-classical monocyte that lacks expression of a mhc-ii complex.
a taste receptor cell that is characterized by morphologically identifiable synaptic contacts with the gustatory nerve fibers and expression of the synaptic membrane protein-25 (snap-25) and ncam.
a smooth muscle cell that is part of the tracheobronchial tree.
a type of type 3 cone bipolar cell with distinctive crescent-shaped dendrites.

a bipolar neuron found in the retina that is synapsed by rod photoreceptor cells. these neurons have axons that arborize and synapse to targets in inner plexiform layers 4 and 5 and depolarize in response to light.

sperm: smooth muscle cell of high endothelial venule of lymph node
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: a layer of smooth muscle cells that forms the outer layer of the high endothelial venule of lymph node and pumps to allow flow of lymph fluid carrying lymphocytes.
a motor neuron that passes from the spinal cord toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes movement.
a bipolar neuron found in the retina and having connections with cone photoreceptor cells and neurons in the inner plexiform layer.

sperm: endothelial cell of efferent lymphatic vessel
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: a(n) endothelial cell that is part of a(n) efferent lymphatic vessel.
a monostratified retinal ganglion cell with large soma and large dendritic field, with medium dendritic arbor, and has dendrites in layers 2 and 5.
a g4 retinal ganglion cell that has post sympatic terminals in sublaminar layers s2 and s3 and is depolarized by decreased illumination of their receptive field center
a bistratified amacrine cell with a medium dendritic field and post-synaptic terminals in s1-s2, and s4.
epidermal cell rich in mitochondria. in amphibians, appears during metamorphosis.

a progenitor cell that can give rise to plasmacytoid and myeloid dendritic cells, and to monocytes and macrophages. marker for this cell is kit-high, cd115-positive, cd135-positive, cx3cr1-positive, and is il7ra-negative.
a effector t cell that provides help in the form of secreted cytokines to other immune cells.

a b220-low cd38-positive naive b cell is a cd38-positive naive b cell that has the phenotype b220-low, cd38-positive, surface igd-positive, surface igm-positive, and cd27-negative, that has not yet been activated by antigen in the periphery.

sperm: basal epithelial cell of prostatic duct
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: a cell that constitutes the basal layer of epithelium in the prostatic duct.
a columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell is a cell usually found in a two dimensional sheet with a free surface. columnar/cuboidal epithelial cells take on the shape of a column or cube.

a double-positive thymocyte that is undergoing positive selection, has high expression of the alpha-beta t cell receptor, is cd69-positive, and is in the process of down regulating the cd8 co-receptor.
an epithelial cell that is part of a umbilical artery.

a neurecto-epithelial cell that is part of the basal layer of the subcommissural organ and specializes in the secretion of proteins into the subarachnoid space. hypendymal cells have similar characteristics to ependymal cells and express sco-spondin.
a goblet cell that is part of the epithelium of bronchus.
a bistratifed retinal amacrine cell with a small dendritic field, dendrite stratification in s1-s2, and a second dendrite stratification in s5.
a peptide hormone secreting cell that secretes vasopressin stimulating hormone
gr1-high monocyte that lacks mhc-ii receptor complex.
a motor neuron that synapses to parasympathetic neurons that innervate tear glands, sweat glands, and the smooth muscles and glands of the pulmonary, cardiovascular, and gastrointestinal systems.
a neuron that has its soma in the heart.

a cell of a fetus which is suspended in the amniotic fluid. amniocytes are considered to arise from several tissues including fetal skin, the fetal urinary tract, umbilical cord, and the inner amniotic surface.
an epithelial cell that is part of the nephron.

an epithelial cell of the medullary thymus. this cell type expresses a diverse range of tissue-specific antigens. this promiscuous gene expression is a cell-autonomous property of medullary epithelial cells and is maintained during the entire period of thymic t cell output.

an interrenal epithelial kidney cell is an epithelial cell found in the anterior kidney of teleosts fish. this cell type is arranged in layers around the posterior cardinal vein and contains many mitochondria with tubulovesicular cristae. interrenal chromaffin cells are interspersed among the tissue layer created by this cell type.
a monostratified retinal ganglion cell that has a small dendrite field with a dense dendrite arbor with post synaptic terminals in sublaminer layer s4.
a type 5 cone bipolar cell with narrowly stratified post synaptic terminals.
a large pre-b-ii cell is a pre-b-ii cell that is proliferating and is rag1-negative and rag2-negative.
a spore formed following meiosis. sometimes following meiosis, prospores may undergo one or more rounds of mitosis before they are fully mature.
a retinal ganglion cell c inner that has dense dendritic diversity.
granule cell that is part of the cerebral cortex.
a neuroendocrine cell that is part of the prostate epithelium.

this is a cell found in the gastrointestinal tract of mammals and serves as a pacemaker that triggers gut contraction. iccs mediate inputs from the enteric nervous system to smooth muscle cells and are thought to be the cells from which gastrointestinal stromal tumors (gists) arise.
a be cell that facilitates development of t-helper 1 (th1) phenotype in cd4-positive t cells, and secretes high levels of interleukin-2, tumor necrosis factor-alpha and interferon-gamma.
a cell of the transparent layer of simple cuboidal epithelium over the anterior surface of the lens. transform into lens fiber(s).

sperm: neuroendocrine cell of epithelium of lobar bronchus
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: a(n) neuroendocrine cell that is part of a(n) epithelium of lobar bronchus.

sperm: basal cell of epithelium of bronchus
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: a basal cell found in the bronchus epithelium.

a neuron that is responsible for sensation in the face or motor functions such as biting and chewing. trigeminal neurons extend a single axon shaft along the lateral white matter of the hindbrain and spinal cord. the highly branched axons innervate the integument of the head.
any melanocyte of skin that is part of a skin of prepuce of penis.

sperm: naive thymus-derived cd4-positive, alpha-beta t cell
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: an antigen inexperienced cd4-positive, alpha-beta t cell with the phenotype ccr7-positive, cd127-positive and cd62l-positive. this cell type develops in the thymus. this cell type is also described as being cd25-negative, cd62l-high, and cd44-low.
a kisspeptin neuron that is located in the dentate gyrus of the hippocampus.

a macrophage which develops from an inflammatory monocyte and is recruited into the tissues in response to injury and infection as part of an inflammatory response. markers include cd11b-positive, cd68-positive, and f4/80-positive.
an epithelial cell scattered in the cortex, predominant in the outer cortex with a large pale nucleus and a prominent nucleolus.

sperm: epithelial cell of proximal tubule segment 2
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: epithelial cell that is part of segment 2 (s2) of the proximal tubule epithelium.

sperm: effector memory cd8-positive, alpha-beta t cell
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: cd8-positive, alpha-beta memory t cell with the phenotype ccr7-negative, cd127-positive, cd45ra-negative, cd45ro-positive, and cd25-negative.
the earliest cytologically identifiable precursor in the thrombocytic series. this cell is capable of endomitosis and lacks expression of hematopoieitic lineage markers (lin-negative).
neuron that secretes the neurotransmitter galanin.
a vgamma1.1-positive, vdelta6.3-negative thymocyte that is cd24-positive.

sperm: epithelial cell of late distal convoluted tubule
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: an epithelial cell located in the late distal convoluted tubule.
a progenitor cell that is capable of forming colonies of primitive erythrocytes in the blood island of the yolk sac. first arrive at e7.5 in mouse and expresses cd41.

sperm: internal epithelial cell of tympanic membrane
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: an extremely flattened cell type found on the inner side of the tympanic membrane. the surface of this cell type carries sparse pleomorphic microvilli that are more common near the junctional zones.

sperm: nkp44-negative group 3 innate lymphoid cell, human
a mature male germ cell that develops fr: a group 3 innate lymphoid cell in the human with the phenotype il-7ralpha-positive, and nkp44-negative.
